Class GroundOverlay

java.lang.Object
  org.osmdroid.views.overlay.Overlay
      org.osmdroid.bonuspack.overlays.GroundOverlay
All Implemented Interfaces:
org.osmdroid.views.util.constants.OverlayConstants
public class GroundOverlay
extends org.osmdroid.views.overlay.Overlay

A ground overlay is an image that is fixed to a map. Mimics the GroundOverlay class from Google Maps Android API v2 as much as possible. Main differences:
- Doesn't support: Z-Index, setPositionFromBounds
- image can be any standard Android Drawable, instead of the BitmapDescriptor introduced in Maps API.

Author:
M.Kergall
See Also:
Google Maps GroundOverlay
